Additional student engagement opportunities include the following options:       Information Session   Information Sessions  Information session provides a more formal setting to promote your organization and your employment opportunities. These would typically be located in one of the lecture rooms in our student center. Space is limited and reservations must be made through the UIC Career Services Office. Requests may be submitted through UICcareers.com. You may also request this service by contacting Cindy Graham, Assistant Director for Employer Relations, at cgraham1@uic.edu or (312) 355-4047.       Information Table   Information Tables  Employers use this to promote employment opportunities in a highly visible area located in our student center. Space is limited and reservation requests are made by contacting the UIC Careers Office by telephone or contacting us directly via email.       Need More Information   Need More Information?  The Employer Relations Team would be happy to tell you more about our great students and discuss what recruiting options work best for your organization and employment needs.       Your UIC Employer Relations Team:      Jaime
    
